						               													<description>Revolta em San Villano is a print and play game in the same setting as Eduardo Guerra's earlier game Her&amp;oacute;is de San Villano. Players are superheroes who have to keep the order in their cit while trying not to upset the general population.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is a roll and write game in which players draw on a common city map. Using one of the five dice from a dice board, they can either draw various icons onto the map or trace a route through the city. A die that is taken from the die board is rerolled and added to a queue, while the first die from the queue replaces the one that was taken from the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When tracing routes to the icons drawn, players gain points for saving innocents, tracking down criminals and so on. But whenever their traces cross, the population gets more upset, and when the revolt marker hits the maximum, the game ends and the player with most points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
